 and in the past, he always manages to almost get killed because he tries to dot a mob or smack them as they run by.  I always tell him to just sit down and take the xp, but he never seems to remember the last time we did the exact same thing and he died horribly.  So, like usual, he goes right into the fray and smacks a spec to &quot;help out&quot;  Of course, all 4 aggro him, and I have to run up and flux/nuke/jiggle-my-booty to get them back on me.  I left one on him just to teach him a lesson, and he proceeded to start loading up dots and fear.<br><br>This was the messed up part.  I have heard of specs doing this before, but I had never seen it.  Even though my brother had like 1 red bub of health and 3 dot/debuffs on the spec, it just couldn't resist lifetapping, then slashing to death every single person that wandered by.  The thing never even missed a step.  Newbies  were dropping like flies as the spectre would just mow them down.  Needless to say, that was the last time that I did specs on dry land. <br><br>Anyway, the moral of the story is:<br><br>Specs are mean.  They like to kill newbies.  I recommend quadding specs underwater.<br><br><br>EDIT:  I removed the flamebait material.  Summar made me feel like crap.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urashakra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rashakra</A> at: 10/17/01 10:52:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usummar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Summar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/16/01 11:24:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> Since I don’t think killing “lowbies” is all that hilarious, I simply went to 