   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> I've been quadding spectres in Oasis and OOT.<br><br>Oasis is tougher due to undead adds and those characters that wander too close to get a look.<br><br>OOT is nice and, relatively, deserted. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I normally quad at spec isle but I've pulled them to the AC isle before.  It is definitely easier to quad there with the flat terrain.<br><br>When will these turn green and are there better alternatives for quick exp.? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=klumhru>Klumhru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/19/01 3:05:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> Why did I do OOT 45-49?<br><br>If you lev a bit on the island and take a look at the topography, you'll notice several points on the island that are level with each other. Spires, hills and the flat top of the island. Just kill all the gargoyles till there are only skellys on the island, since the skellys don't aggro, but the gargs always do, all the way up to 49...<br><br>225int + 380mana at the time, I had no problem keeping up with their 6 minute spawn time. I went from 40 to 50 in 8 days, after getting invite to Valhall (My local semiuber guild) when I hit 50. I feel sorry for the nonquading punts.<br><br>Klumhru<br>56 Evoker / Veeshan<br>Beornulf<br>51 Champion / Bristlebane <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=91376"><img src="http://www.snigel.org/klumhru/klumhru.jpg" border="0"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufirion69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Firion69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/25/01 3:25:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> Note for kiting the bloodgills: For pulling all 4, just take another pullinground, simple as that. <br>Pull one at pillar, swim to under platform, flux, hit the water and outrun the two following you, swim down to pillar flux gobbo swim to other pillar flux the last gobbo, run to beach, kill.<br>(Done with swim skill maxed or close to maxed tho, if its not maxed they catch you in the water)<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rolfe>rolfe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/12/01 12:29:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> I think the genius is the gal that missed the sarcasm in rashakra's story.  He wasn't saying that killing newbies is fun OR funny.  What he DID say was that his story had a moral, and that moral amounted to staying AWAY from newbies when killing specs.<br><br>It was a good story, Rashakra.<br><br>Rolfe of Povar <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rolfe>rolfe</A> at: 11/12/01 12:30:26 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urashakra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rashakra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/13/01 9:24:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.pcis.net/gurvy/gecko/lettuce.jpeg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the support, hehe.<br><br>My original post did mention the situation being hilarious, but I kinda cut that out. =/<br><br>I meant the post to be informative and to make sure that people are careful when doing wizardly things... (near suicidal kites just to get faster-than-hell xp)<br><br>It was funny I guess because i had flashbacks to the first time my brother got his iksar to oasis (8th level) only to be immediately cut down by a spectre at the dock and we spent the next couple hours running him back over again.  THAT was entertainment.  LOL<br><br>Rash <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uibun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ibun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/26/01 6:00:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> I usually quad the oasis spec's in the SW corner, by that little orc camp or whatever and the dwarf npc. I hardly ever see any lowb's around there, only had one instance in 43-44, where lowb's were at the camp, but they didn't aggro. and if there's someone in that area, there's some level &quot;runways&quot; like the one that goes by the sro zone (not that many lowb's there) or a side of a dune south of the inn. Plus it helps to round them up in the water and then bring them straight onto land.<br>I've also timed the CoF refreshes so that they are, or fraction of a second from, being in range, which is usually about 1-2sec of running straight after casting with sow potion, so I'm able to finish by the time I pass Sro (from the SW corner).<br>Just my 2cp<br><br>Ibun<br>44th Ring of Fire<br>Knights of Velious<br>Luclin Server  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uslimbhcarvul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slimb Hcarvul</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/29/01 5:25:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://208.180.232.40/eq/family/images/heads/slimb_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> Whenever I'm quadding specs in oasis (usually while waiting on raft to TD).  I will shout to zone what i'm quadding and where (near SRO/inn) and to be careful when running in that area.  I also let em know that the quickest way to die generally is getting too close or trying to help.  I have yet to run into any dead lowbies who listened to this advice. <p><b><strong>Slimb <br><BR><u>23rd</u> Norse Spiritmaster (Slim)<br><u>9th</U> Briton Friar (Slimb)<BR><u>48th</u> Erudite Wizard (Slimb Hcarvul)</strong></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufalen14.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falen14</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/7/02 9:20:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> Hey guys any chance you can throw the tactics used for multi-kiting the specs here on thsi post. Including which spells, buffs and what not you use for lvl 48+<br><br> As you can probably tell I am new to the quad kiting thing so this will be very helpful. Thanks. <p>Dont meddle in the affair of wizards, for they are secret and quick to anger!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubranamanstarbinder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Branaman Starbinder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/14/02 4:11:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> I always pulled them to the orc camp on the highway in the corner of the zone. 