take 2-3 rounds of 4 lifetaps.  The extra HPs from the shielding spell is nice as well.  <br><br>Flux pull 4, round up in water.  Drag the set onto land and snare.  If you're fast on a resist you can snare the resisters and regroup then for a full snare.  If you wait even 20 seconds, you're better off just med-kiting (with no damage output) until BoF wears off an rerounding up.<br><br>I like using the water's edge area, with an F9 view hanging out over the water.  Easy to see what I'm doing.<br>At L45, 198 INT and about 60 in +mana (sad, I know) I can drop the whole quad in -1- BoF if I intersperse 2-3 Column of Lightnings in to the Circle of Force.  While Circle of Force is more mana-efficient, the extra couple Columns will allow you to not have to resnare unless something goes amiss.<br><br>If you get 2 dead, and 2 left, and you're VLOM, root one, back off, and harvest.   Once you break up the duo and they're low on health they'll get out of &quot;social&quot; range of each other and into hold/flee mode.  Don't let them regen to the point that they re-agro, but you can harvest/med up, DD one, root the other again, and finish it.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Spell Load</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>Shock of Lightning<br>Enstill (Longer hold than root)<br>Bonds of Force<br>Column of Lightning<br>Circle of Force<br>Harvest<br>Yonder<br>Gate<br><br>For adds, simply ensill the add and quad the specs away from it.   Usually you can get out of range of the add before enstill breaks, but if it comes back just re-enstill, finish the quad, and deal with it(kill/zone).  If you get an add, obviously, you'll have to re BoF the quad at some point.<br><br>1.2-2.0 blues per quad at level 44, about 0.8 blues per quad at 45.  Hopefully that'll go back up to at least 1.0-1.5 at 46, but we'll see.<br><br>Specs have 10gp-4pp each, and scythes which range from 1gp - 10pp. (Rusty-bronze-regular)  I'm getting a LOT of runes/words/pages from the quads, too.  Much higher drop rate than anything in OT.<br><br>-Szii Uln'hyrr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/3/02 11:21:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs</span><hr size=1> I pulled specs in Oasis till the tower pulls were not too bad, then I want to OOT and the spawn timer and mana regen were perfect, and they are the same type of specs as are in the tower, not around the island. You can tell the difference by the tint of their &quot;face&quot;.<br><br>I would warn people I was pulling specs and that was usually enough. Occationally I would get someone helping who didn't ask first. I would apologise after they died that I couln't help them, and ask them not to do it again as I may not be able to clean up the mess because of it. And yes, I would laugh my ass off if they walked into a spec.<br><br>Now here is the strangest thing I ever saw:<br>Textbook Quad south of the lake in Oasis. Was only last nuke or 2 and all 4 specs turn to an orc warrior wandering nearby, and lifetap it to death. Never saw anything like it before or since.<br><br> <p>Baroness Ennya Dragonslayer<BR>1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>Champion Slayer, WurmSlayer<BR>WurmHunter<BR>Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">